<item>
            <title>[OAK-8262] CompiledPermissionImpl returns wrong type of TreePermission for child of permission store </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-8262</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;while working on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-8240&quot; title=&quot;Improve test coverage for org.apache.jackrabbit.oak.security.authorization.permission&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-8240&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-8240&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; i noticed that &lt;tt&gt;CompiledPermissionImpl&lt;/tt&gt; will return the wrong type of &lt;tt&gt;TreePermission&lt;/tt&gt; for subtrees of the permission storage as it wrongly computes the tree type to be DEFAULT instead of INTERNAL.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
