                            <comment id="16830260" author="anchela" created="Tue, 30 Apr 2019 12:49:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stillalex&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stillalex&quot;&gt;stillalex&lt;/a&gt;, proposed patch attached to fix this. the key problem is that i returned TreePermission.EMPTY for the internal type and subsequently the parent-type will no longer be properly determined as internal. introducing dedicated internal-tree-permission that returns the same as EMPTY (except for the childPermission) should IMO do the trick. wdyt?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
